      • catalogName

        Name of catalog.

      • catalogAuthor

        public java.lang.String catalogAuthor

      • catalogDescription

        public java.lang.String catalogDescription
        Catalog description.

      • beam

        public float beam
        Beam of instrument in arcseconds, that can be used to search around an object inside the beam.

      • fields

        public java.lang.String[][] fields
        Fields of the catalog formatted as identifier (for development purposes), a blank space separator, and the name of the field as Vizier gives it for a given catalog. First index is table index, since a given catalog could have several tables. Second is field index.

      • bands

        public PhotometricBandElement[] bands
        Photometric bands used by the catalog. The name of the band should be set to the name of the field that holds the flux for this band. The corresponding flux error field name should be the same name as the flux plus the string "_ERROR".

      • data

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String[]> data
        Holds data retrieved from Vizier as a set of String arrays.

      • dataFields

        public java.lang.String[] dataFields
        Fields of the catalog as Vizier gives them.

      • unit

        public java.lang.String[] unit
        Hold the units for the fluxes.

      • links

        public java.lang.String[] links
        Holds links to be added to certain fields when representing a table. Format is the field name, a space, an the link structure. Any other field can be inserted in the structure with the field name between html tags.

      • getFluxesAsSpectrum

        public Spectrum getFluxesAsSpectrum(java.lang.String bandName,
                           boolean allFluxes,
                           boolean use_ESA_method)
                             throws JPARSECException
        Obtains the fluxes for a given Vizier element as an spectrum.
        Parameters:
        bandName - Band name to get the fluxes from. Can be null to retrieve all fluxes available.
        allFluxes - Defines what fluxes to get, all (true) or the first found (false).
        use_ESA_method - Method to apply for Tycho catalog (ESA or Kidger).
        Returns:
        Array of Strings with wavelength in cm, flux in mJy, flux error, the band name and the band beam, separated by blank spaces.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • getFluxes

        public java.lang.String[] getFluxes(java.lang.String bandName,
                           boolean allFluxes,
                           boolean use_ESA_method)
                             throws JPARSECException
        Obtains the fluxes for a given Vizier element.
        Parameters:
        bandName - Band name to get the fluxes from. Can be null to retrieve all fluxes available.
        allFluxes - Defines what fluxes to get, all (true) or the first found (false).
        use_ESA_method - Method to apply for Tycho catalog (ESA or Kidger).
        Returns:
        Array of Strings with wavelength in cm, flux in mJy, flux error, the band name and the band beam, separated by blank spaces.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • setTableIndex

        public void setTableIndex(int index)
        Sets the table index for this Vizier object. This value is automatically set in JPARSEC by means of the VizierQuery.readVOTable(cds.savot.model.SavotVOTable, jparsec.observer.LocationElement).
        Parameters:
        index - The table index, 0 for the first (default value), 1 for the second, and so on.

      • getTableIndex

        public int getTableIndex()
        Returns the table index number for this Vizier object. 0 means the first table in the catalog, 1 the second, and so on. Most catalogs only contains 1 table so this value will be 0 most of the times.
        Returns:
        Table index number.
